cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for traffic scene understanding, specifically for traffic lane detection. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new type of CNN called Spatial CNN (SCNN), which involves message passing between pixels across rows and columns in a layer, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of SCNN for object detection and segmentation, which could fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training and optimizing the SCNN, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
